race.description: Landlord Insure By Corpsure C,G&E Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: CHARLIE TANGO (8) wasted no time getting off the mark on debut over 1000m at this track four weeks ago. Will come on following that run and looks tough to hold out again. HOLLYWOOD EPIC (1) was an emphatic winner last time over this trip on the Poly with today's rider Leah Martyn engaged. Has the pace to cross from the wide draw and the 3kg claimer aids the big weight. Can go close. CANAVESE (7) is a progressive type returning. Fitter for recent trials and is a noted fresh performer. Is drawn to advantage and is expected to make his presence felt. WARILLA GORILLA (6) is another resuming, and has been readied with two trial wins. Worth noting he was a dominant maiden winner when resuming last time in. Can make a bright return. INNERVISIONS (4) let punters down last start at Ipswich when going under at short odds. That followed a good first-up win at Beaudesert. Has his share of talent, worth another chance third-up.
